# VoteFight Security Guidelines

## Authentication & Authorization
- Always validate user permissions before actions
- Use JWT tokens for authentication
- Implement proper session management
- Validate all user inputs
- Use HTTPS for all communications

## Vote Fraud Prevention
- Track IP addresses and browser fingerprints
- Implement vote cooldown periods
- Use session-based tracking for shared IPs
- Validate vote authenticity
- Implement CAPTCHA for suspicious activity
- Log all voting activities for audit

## File Security
- Encrypt all uploaded files
- Use time-limited access URLs
- Validate file types and sizes
- Scan files for malware
- Implement secure file storage
- Use CDN with proper headers

## API Security
- Validate all API inputs
- Use proper HTTP status codes
- Implement CORS correctly
- Use API rate limiting
- Log all API requests
- Implement proper error handling

## Database Security
- Use parameterized queries
- Implement proper database permissions
- Encrypt sensitive data
- Use database connection pooling
- Implement proper backup strategies
- Monitor database access

## Content Security
- Implement content moderation
- Use AI for inappropriate content detection
- Implement user reporting system
- Validate all user-generated content
- Implement proper data retention policies